Package: rmatio
Title: A R package to read and write matlab files
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Christopher", "Hulbert",
    role = c("aut"),
    comment = "Author of the C-library matio, http://sourceforge.net/projects/matio/")
    person("Stefan", "Widgren",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "stefan.widgren@sva.se",
    comment = "Author of the R interface to the C-library matio"))
Description: rmatio is a package for reading and writing Matlab MAT
             files from R, using the C MAT File I/O Library matio
             written by Christopher Hulbert
             (http://sourceforge.net/projects/matio/).
Copyright: The package uses the source code of matio written by
           Christopher Hulbert (http://sourceforge.net/projects/matio/)
           (License: Simplified BSD). The matio io routines have
           been adopted to use R printing and error routines.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/stewid/rmatio
Type: Package
LazyLoad: yes
Date: 2013-08-25
Depends:
    R(>= 2.15.2),
    Matrix,
    methods,
    lattice
Suggests:
    testthat
Collate:
    'read_mat.r'
    'write_mat.r'
